1
00:00:00,284 --> 00:00:04,453
Okay, so we can begin our practice by just sitting quietly.

2
00:00:12,775 --> 00:00:15,441
And once we're a little settled.

3
00:00:29,832 --> 00:00:38,905
So just a little opening meta, just to bring someone to mind whom we have a natural or an easy, warm regard for.

4
00:00:40,426 --> 00:00:45,814
Just as they come into your mind, just to offer them from the heart your good wishes.

5
00:00:48,459 --> 00:00:50,881
May you be safe, well and happy.

6
00:00:51,843 --> 00:00:55,789
May you live contented in harmony with the world.

7
00:01:13,453 --> 00:01:17,218
We can bring to mind those who are near and dear to us.

8
00:01:35,966 --> 00:01:40,373
We can bring to mind friends, people at work, whomever we wish.

9
00:02:02,763 --> 00:02:06,462
There's also a neutral person, someone we see but don't know.

10
00:02:31,602 --> 00:02:34,491
turning the stream of compassion towards ourselves.

11
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:03,312
Opening outwards towards each other.

12
00:03:30,022 --> 00:03:33,608
radiating outwards to our neighbors and neighborhood.

13
00:03:55,219 --> 00:03:57,263
To all the people in our country,

14
00:04:21,103 --> 00:04:45,653
All the peoples of York.

15
00:04:45,673 --> 00:04:47,095
All people on ice.

16
00:05:11,088 --> 00:05:14,391
and to all beings in all directions.

17
00:05:34,694 --> 00:05:37,516
So we can begin now with forgivingness.

18
00:05:37,716 --> 00:05:42,925
We're working first of all with people who we've upset, we've hurt in some way.

19
00:05:43,668 --> 00:05:45,610
So remember, you don't have to go for the big one.

20
00:05:46,492 --> 00:05:50,059
It can be somebody who's not so bad.

21
00:05:50,959 --> 00:05:59,375
So as that person, as that event comes to mind, see what comes up in the heart, observe your relationship to what comes up.

22
00:06:00,978 --> 00:06:02,661
Someone whom we have hurt.

23
00:06:35,512 --> 00:06:37,375
Careful not to let the mind wander.

24
00:06:48,612 --> 00:06:53,639
Be honest about what you're experiencing, the hurt, the guilt, the shame, etc.

25
00:07:06,394 --> 00:07:07,598
Sense of remorse.

26
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:20,725
There's also that self-righteousness, they deserved it.

27
00:07:41,528 --> 00:07:45,531
Oh, just acknowledging that all these mental states are unwholesome.

28
00:08:07,370 --> 00:08:09,492
And just as the heart begins to mellow

29
00:08:11,329 --> 00:08:15,687
Perhaps you feel it's the time just to ask for forgiveness.

30
00:08:56,504 --> 00:09:01,975
Just picturing them in your mind, talking to them, telling them how you feel.

31
00:09:10,894 --> 00:09:13,499
And you bring yourself round to saying, please forgive me.

32
00:09:15,383 --> 00:09:16,284
I'm sorry.

33
00:09:46,657 --> 00:09:51,065
Perhaps you can see them forgiving you if you've got an imagination.

34
00:09:57,456 --> 00:10:00,361
And if so, can you let their love back in?

35
00:10:24,355 --> 00:10:27,899
And at some point to wish them well.

36
00:10:49,687 --> 00:10:51,408
And just allow them to fade away.

37
00:11:06,610 --> 00:11:10,274
Of course, when you're doing these practices yourself, you can take your time.

38
00:11:11,837 --> 00:11:17,605
But here we're just touching into them.

39
00:11:17,625 --> 00:11:19,568
So now is the time to forgive others.

40
00:11:19,808 --> 00:11:22,413
So bringing somebody to mind who's upset us.

41
00:11:23,815 --> 00:11:32,567
And again, just as they come into the mind, that event, just to hold it fairly steady, to get in touch with what comes up.

42
00:11:32,587 --> 00:11:35,131
The hurt, the desire for revenge, all that sort of stuff.

43
00:11:36,749 --> 00:11:38,432
and how you're relating to that.

44
00:11:43,283 --> 00:11:52,783
Somebody has upset us.

45
00:12:21,282 --> 00:12:24,308
I always think noting can be very useful at these times.

46
00:12:24,369 --> 00:12:27,918
You sort of say, well, this is how hurt feels.

47
00:12:27,957 --> 00:12:30,302
This is how anger feels.

48
00:12:31,647 --> 00:12:34,312
Just so that we're very honest with ourselves.

49
00:13:00,432 --> 00:13:07,253
And then at some point to begin to feel that maybe you can forgive them.

50
00:13:26,926 --> 00:13:30,368
And you can say, you know, I'm not going to take advantage.

51
00:13:30,388 --> 00:13:31,856
I'm not going to get my own back.

52
00:14:06,835 --> 00:14:21,253
When we say to somebody, I forgive you, sometimes it feels as though it's coming from a sort of prideful place, you know, like I forgive you, like somebody in high power forgiving you, letting you off.

53
00:14:24,616 --> 00:14:32,927
But it is coming from, you know, a heart which wants to reestablish that friendship, reestablish that communication.

54
00:14:35,826 --> 00:14:38,495
Perhaps you can find another way of saying it.

55
00:15:02,049 --> 00:15:08,500
And perhaps you can see in them a sense of really the desire to be reconciled.

56
00:15:38,246 --> 00:15:39,970
And again just wishing them well.

57
00:15:55,155 --> 00:15:56,778
And allowing them to fade away.

58
00:16:10,072 --> 00:16:16,943
And so finally we come to ourselves, remembering the little contemplations there on dependence, origination and karma.

59
00:16:17,985 --> 00:16:26,640
So again, finding something where we've done harm to ourselves.

60
00:16:27,923 --> 00:16:36,537
You know, physically we might have been putting stuff in the body which isn't very good for us, or putting it in dangerous situations.

61
00:16:37,528 --> 00:16:42,775
And the heart, what would be done with what we put into our hearts and through our minds?

62
00:16:43,758 --> 00:16:44,719
What have we watched?

63
00:16:44,839 --> 00:16:49,886
What have we done which has undermined us, has done us harm?

64
00:16:50,868 --> 00:16:55,313
Just choose one that you can sort of feel you can work with.

65
00:17:03,785 --> 00:17:07,131
Just in the same way, just accept totally.

66
00:17:07,921 --> 00:17:15,332
the harm that we've done ourselves, the consequences

67
00:17:43,425 --> 00:17:49,748
And to speak to ourselves gently, you know, that we're ready to accept the consequences.

68
00:17:52,176 --> 00:17:53,160
We can bear them.

69
00:17:53,421 --> 00:17:54,786
We can bear with them.

70
00:18:21,901 --> 00:18:29,153
And all these voices that we might hear of self-recrimination and blaming ourselves and all that.

71
00:18:29,654 --> 00:18:31,458
Again, you just open up to that.

72
00:18:31,817 --> 00:18:33,000
Just receive it.

73
00:18:34,061 --> 00:18:36,686
Just allow those voices to express themselves.

74
00:18:58,469 --> 00:19:01,773
And then some, in a way, to sort of embrace it.

75
00:19:01,894 --> 00:19:04,617
Embrace it with loving kindness.

76
00:19:04,719 --> 00:19:06,361
Embrace it with a sense of care.

77
00:19:06,401 --> 00:19:07,903
This is a part of our hearts.

78
00:19:08,884 --> 00:19:10,586
Our hearts which has turbulence.

79
00:19:10,748 --> 00:19:11,469
It's upset.

80
00:19:12,490 --> 00:19:15,575
And just holding it in that sort of gentle embrace.

81
00:19:20,301 --> 00:19:21,944
And just speaking to ourselves.

82
00:19:22,865 --> 00:19:23,247
Gently.

83
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:23,446
Gently.

84
00:19:43,119 --> 00:19:46,646
Sounds a bit odd, but you can just try, I forgive you.

85
00:19:46,967 --> 00:19:48,009
I forgive myself.

86
00:19:49,491 --> 00:19:52,277
I forgive myself.

87
00:19:52,298 --> 00:19:53,098
How does that feel?

88
00:19:56,285 --> 00:19:57,827
I'm not going to beat myself up any.

89
00:19:58,288 --> 00:19:59,391
I forgive myself.

90
00:20:23,519 --> 00:20:29,851
And then to sort of formulate a resolution, something that you really intend not to do again.

91
00:20:29,871 --> 00:20:33,597
Of course, you might do it again and you have to go through this process.

92
00:20:34,038 --> 00:20:43,738
But the intention is not to behave like, not to do anything like that again to myself and indeed to others.

93
00:21:09,352 --> 00:21:12,057
This brings us to the end of the forgiving practice.

94
00:21:12,218 --> 00:21:17,969
You'll find the notes are more detailed.

95
00:21:19,311 --> 00:21:27,248
And if you go onto the website and go onto resources and e-books, I've written a little book on forgiveness.

96
00:21:27,729 --> 00:21:30,094
Towards the End of Forgiveness, it's called.

97
00:21:30,596 --> 00:21:39,748
and there's a little monologue, Angulimala, if you've never heard it before, you can have a go and listen to that.

98
00:21:41,150 --> 00:21:52,403
So we can sit quietly now, just resting with the heart, and perhaps it's in a good place now, perhaps it feels warm and happy.

99
00:21:52,423 --> 00:21:58,410
If it's not, that's not a problem, we also work with what's there.

